{"article_id":"GDYjPxH9jfKDM5pV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The House of Representatives voted Wednesday to transmit the articles of impeachment against President Trump to the Senate ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"formally paving the way for a historic trial over the president 's dealings with Ukraine","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"after weeks of delay .","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"The resolution ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"which passed 228-193 largely along party lines ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"came nearly a month after lawmakers voted to impeach the president on two counts .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , officially signed the articles Wednesday afternoon during an `` engrossment ceremony . ''","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"Clerk of the House Cheryl Johnson and House Sergeant at Arms Paul Irving walked a note over to the Senate","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"notifying the upper chamber of Congress","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"that Pelosi had signed the articles of impeachment","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"and appointed managers to the trial .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"PELOSI ANNOUNCES","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"HOUSE IMPEACHMENT MANAGERS TO PROSECUTE CASE AGAINST TRUMP","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Rep. Collin Peterson , D-Minn. , was the only Democrat","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"who voted against the resolution .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Rep. Justin Amash , I-Mich. , voted with Democrats .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"There were no Republican defections .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"Pelosi had been holding on to the articles","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"-- charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress --","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"in a bid","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to extract favorable terms for the trial","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"including a commitment on witnesses ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"but she ended her delay","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"after Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell made clear","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"he was not willing to negotiate .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Lawmakers gave impassioned speeches on the House floor in the run-up to the vote .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Pelosi said ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"`` We are here today","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to cross a very important threshold in American history . ''","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"\" When someone is impeached ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"they are always impeached , \"","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"the California Democrat said .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"\" It can not be erased . \"","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy , R-Calif. , ripped into the Democratic efforts ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"saying ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"\" This is not a moment","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"this body should be proud of .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"As Pelosi says ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"impeachment is a national civics lesson .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Let 's use this blunder as a teachable moment . \"","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"\" We wouldn ' t abuse our power","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"just for the sheer sake of politics","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"to say","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"you ' re impeached forever","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"because I dislike you , \"","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"McCarthy added .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Just minutes after the final vote , the White House blasted the articles of impeachment as `` the weakest articles in history . ''","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"`` The only thing","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Speaker Pelosi has achieved with this sham , illegitimate impeachment process ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"is to prove","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"she is focused on politics instead of the American people , ''","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"White House Press Secretary Stephanie Grisham said in a statement Wednesday .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"`` The Speaker lied","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"when she claimed","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"this was urgent and vital to national security","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"because","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"when the articles passed ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"she held them for an entire month in an egregious effort","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"to garner political support .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"She failed","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"and the naming of these managers does not change a single thing . '' `` President Trump has done nothing wrong , ''","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"she continued .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"`` He looks forward to having the due process rights in the Senate","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"that Speaker Pelosi and House Democrats denied to him ,","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and expects to be fully exonerated . \"","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"At the heart of the case is Trump 's effort","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"to convince Ukraine to launch investigations of Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"while his administration withheld military aid .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Trump denies wrongdoing ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"while Democrats allege","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"he abused the power of his office .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"A source familiar with the Senate trial told Fox News","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"when they receive the articles ,","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"there will be several days of pre-trial preparations and procedural steps","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"before launching into a full trial ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"which will likely kick off early next week .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"Pelosi introduced the lawmakers","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"who will serve as House managers","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"to prosecute the case against the president","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"early Wednesday .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"They include House Intelligence Committee Chairman Adam Schiff , D-Calif. ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"who will serve as lead manager","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"and who directed much of the House impeachment inquiry out of his committee ,","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"and House Judiciary Committee Chairman Jerrold Nadler , D-N.Y. ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"whose panel drafted the articles of impeachment .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"Pelosi also tapped House Democratic Caucus Chairman Hakeem Jeffries , D-N.Y. ; Reps. Jason Crow , D-Colo. ; Val Demings , D-Fla. ; Sylvia Garcia , D-Texas ; and Zoe Lofgren , D-Calif .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"Once the Senate notifies the House","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"that the Senate is prepared to receive the managers ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"they will come to an agreement on a specific time","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"for the managers to appear","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"and introduce the case .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"They will read the official resolution ,","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"which the House passed on Wednesday ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"and the articles of impeachment in full .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"TRUMP ' S IMPEACHMENT TRIAL TEAM :","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"WHO ARE THE LAWYERS","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"DEFENDING THE PRESIDENT ?","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"Later in the week , the Senate will notify U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"that they are ready to proceed .","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"At an agreed time , Roberts will arrive","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"and be sworn in by Sen. Chuck Grassley , R-Iowa ,","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"who serves as the president pro tempore of the Senate .","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"Once Roberts is sworn in ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"he will swear in the senators .","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"The senators , at that point , will vote on the `` organizing resolution , ''","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"which will lay out the framework for the trial .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"McConnell , R-Ky. , has repeatedly said","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that the resolution","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"to govern the impeachment trial in the Senate","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"would mirror the one","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"used for then-President Bill Clinton ' s impeachment trial in 1999 .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"That resolution will set a time frame","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"for the trial to begin ,","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"with the opportunity","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"for lawmakers to determine how to proceed on potential witness testimony and additional documents later ,","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"after both the president ' s defense and the prosecution make their opening statements .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"McConnell has insisted","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"that he has the votes","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"to pass the organizing resolution","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"and begin the trial ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"before committing to witness testimony .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"In impeachment , most resolutions can pass with a simple majority .","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"To remove the president from office ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"there must be 67 votes .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"Democrats have repeatedly demanded","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"that witnesses be called for the trial .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"McConnell has vowed to take up the issue of witnesses","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"after the trial has started .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"In remarks to reporters on Tuesday , McConnell suggested","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"that both parties could call preferred witnesses","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"if they go down that road .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"\" We will be able to go through some preliminary steps this week ...","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"which would give us the ability","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"to start the actual trial next Tuesday , \"","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"He went on to say","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"that he would address the issue of potential witnesses at \" the appropriate time , \"","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"and that \" both sides will call witnesses","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"they want to hear from . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":279,"left":150,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":142,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":141,"right":2,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":144,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":143,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":6,"right":147,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":147,"left":7,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":8,"right":145,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":145,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":278,"left":203,"right":277,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":163,"right":202,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":163,"left":151,"right":162,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":154,"right":161,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":153,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":152,"right":15,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":158,"right":160,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":155,"right":1